  "instructions": [
    "In a large pot or Dutch oven, heat 2 tablespoons of oil over medium-high heat.",
    "Add the beef and cook until browned on all sides, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the onion and red bell pepper and cook until tender, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the garlic, smoked paprika, and jerk seasoning and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add the potatoes, carrots, green beans, beef broth, tomato paste, cocoa powder, brown sugar, salt, and black pepper. Stir to combine.",
    "Bring the stew to a boil, then reduce the heat to medium-low and simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.",
    "Stir in the coconut milk and hot sauce (if using).",
    "Simmer for an additional 10-15 minutes, or until the flavors have melded together and the beef is tender.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with chopped fresh cilantro (if desired)."
